  • Method Details

    • find

      public int find(Member member)
      Find the member is in the member list.
      Parameters:
      member - member to find.
      Returns:
      index of the list if the member is found, -1 if not found.

    • getMember

      public Member getMember(Member member)
      Same as the find but return Member instead of index. return New member instead of existing one to avoid bug.
      Parameters:
      member - member to find.
      Returns:
      Member object if the member is found, null if not found.

    • findGetter

      public int findGetter(Member member)
      Getter method to use find in other classes.
      Parameters:
      member - member to find.
      Returns:
      result of the find method.

    • grow

      private void grow()
      If the list is full of the members, increase the capacity of the list. It creates new array with 4 more size and copy contents from the original list.

    • sizeGetter

      public int sizeGetter()
      getter method that gets current size of the list.
      Returns:
      size of the list.

    • add

      public boolean add(Member member)
      Add the member to the member list. It automatically grows if the array is full.
      Parameters:
      member - member to be added.
      Returns:
      false if member is already in the list, true if the member is added.

    • remove

      public boolean remove(Member member)
      Remove the member from the list.
      Parameters:
      member - member to be removed from the list.
      Returns:
      false if member is not in the list, true if the member is removed from the list.

    • print

      public void print()
      Print the list of the member as-is. State that the list is empty if there is no one in the list.

    • printByCounty

      public void printByCounty()
      Print the list sorted by zipcode.

    • sortByCountry

      private void sortByCountry()
      Sort the member list by zipcode. Helper method for printByCounty().

      public void printByExpirationDate()

    • printByName

      Print the member list sorted by the name.

    • printWithFee

      public void printWithFee()
      Print method with membership fee.

    • sortByName

      private void sortByName()
      Sort the member list by the name of the member. Last name first and then first name. Helper method for printByName().

    • fitnessParticipants

      public String[] fitnessParticipants()
      Get the String format of the participants of fitness class. Used different method because the format is slightly different.
      Returns:
      Array of Strings contains participants of the fitness class.
